<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7B164A78E8FC50278BFC5D" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7B164A78E8FC50278BFC5D" blockId="11.[136,1452,806,1337]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A78E8FC5026CAFC05" bold="true" box="[189,400,914,940]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7B164A79F9FC50251CFC05" authorityName="A. Saint-Hilaire &amp; Naudin" authorityYear="1842" box="[428,582,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lonchitis">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A79F9FC50251CFC05" box="[428,582,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Sida lonchitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished from other species of section 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7B164A7C00FC5023C9FC05" box="[1109,1171,914,940]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Sidae">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7C00FC5023C9FC05" box="[1109,1171,914,940]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Sidae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7B164A7CF7FC5023ACFC05" box="[1186,1270,914,940]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
) by the flowers arranged in glomerules and by the presence of bifid bracts (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7B164A7B4AFC742498FC79" box="[799,962,950,976]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="10.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[248,1340,353,1895]" captionTargetId="figure-118@10.[248,1340,353,1895]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–F. Sida farroupilhensis. A. Flower. B. Abaxial surface of leaf. C. Adaxial surface of leaf. D. Mature schizocarp. E. Mature and immature schizocarps. F. Branch with leaves and flowers buds. G–J Sida linifolia. G. Abaxial surface of leaf. H. Buds in terminal umbelliform inflorescence. I. Schizocarps and buds in terminal umbelliform inflorescence J. Branch with flowers and buds. K–Q. Sida lonchitis. K. Flowers. L, N. Adaxial surface of leaf. M. Abaxial surface of leaf. O. Terminal inflorescence. P. Bifid bracts (black arrow). Q. Schizocarps. Photographs I–J by Luís Funez, all others by Martin Grings (G–J from N.I. Matzenbacher, ICN 123026)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415495" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415495/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Figures 4K–Q</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7B164A7B9BFC7424AEFC79" box="[974,1012,950,976]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">14I</figureCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A7C5FFC7423BDFC79" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[1034,1255,950,976]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" pagination="193 - 208" refId="ref19497" refString="Krapovickas, A. (2007 a) Novedades en el genero Sida (Malvaceae, Tribu Malveae). Bonplandia 16: 193 - 208. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 163 - 4147" type="journal article" year="2007">Krapovickas 2007a</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A7CA7FC74279FFC5D" author="Yoshikawa, V. N. &amp; Duarte, M. C. &amp; Goncalez, V. M." pageId="11" pageNumber="116" pagination="184 - 188" refId="ref20749" refString="Yoshikawa, V. N., Duarte, M. C. &amp; Goncalez, V. M. (2019) Sida uniaristata, a new species of Sida sect. Sidae L. (Malvaceae, Malvoideae) from Brazil. Systematic Botany 44: 184 - 188. https: // doi. org / 10.1600 / 036364419 X 698001" type="journal article" year="2019">
Yoshikawa 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A7D21FC7522F6FC79" box="[1396,1452,950,976]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">et al.</emphasis>
2019
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B7B164A78E8FC3C2635FB65" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B7B164A78E8FC3C2635FB65" blockId="11.[136,1452,806,1337]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A78E8FC3C2587FBB1" bold="true" box="[189,733,1022,1048]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—The species occurs in southeast, south, and “Distrito Federal” of 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7B164A78F3FBE027B0FB95" box="[166,234,1058,1084]" name="Brazil" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7B164A78ADFBE026D3FB95" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[248,393,1058,1084]" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). The species is mentioned to 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7B164A7A86FBE02418FB95" box="[723,834,1058,1084]" name="Argentina" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Argentina</collectingCountry>
by Krapovickas (2007), but without a voucher. In State of Rio Grande do Sul 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7B164A79D6FB85255AFBC9" authorityName="A. Saint-Hilaire &amp; Naudin" authorityYear="1842" box="[387,512,1094,1121]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Malvaceae" genus="Sida" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malvales" pageId="11" pageNumber="116" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lonchitis">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7B164A79D6FB85255AFBC9" box="[387,512,1094,1121]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">S. lonchitis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recorded only in Tropical Forest (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7B164A7BE2FB842340FBC9" box="[951,1050,1094,1120]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[262,1350,253,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[199,1389,190,1947]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of Sida anomala, S. cerradoensis, S. confusa, S. cordifolia, S. dubia, S. farroupilhensis and S. lonchitis in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415491/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="116">Figure 2</figureCitation>
), in edges or ruderal environments. With the available records, the species presents an EOO of 1,030,158.204 Km² and an AOO of 120 Km². Although it can be considered EN by the AOO, conditions B(a), B(b) and B(c) were not met. Thus, the species is here considered Least Concern (LC).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
